Relationship between cognitive function and regional cerebral blood flow in Alzheimer's disease. The Mini-Mental State examination (MMSE) is frequently used to assess the cognitive function of neurological patients. The purpose of this study was to investigate associations between regional cerebral blood flow (rCBF) and MMSE scores in Alzheimer's disease (AD) and localization of cognitive functions. Fifty-nine patients with probable AD (21 males and 38 females mean age 74 years) and 12 normal volunteers (five males and seven females